            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-44003",
              "name": "LanguageSpecificPackageVulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "vm2's Transformer Fast-Path Bypass Exposes Internal State Variable"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "vm2 is an open source vm/sandbox for Node.js. Prior to 3.11.0, vm2's code transformer has a performance optimization that skips AST analysis when the code does not contain catch, import, or async keywords. This fast-path bypass allows sandboxed code to directly access the internal VM2_INTERNAL_STATE_DO_NOT_USE_OR_PROGRAM_WILL_FAIL variable, which exposes internal security functions (handleException, wrapWith, import). This vulnerability is fixed in 3.11.0."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-44003",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-44003\nSeverity: MEDIUM\nPackage: vm2\nFixed Version: 3.11.0\nLink: [CVE-2026-44003](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-44003)\nvm2 is an open source vm/sandbox for Node.js. Prior to 3.11.0, vm2's code transformer has a performance optimization that skips AST analysis when the code does not contain catch, import, or async keywords. This fast-path bypass allows sandboxed code to directly access the internal VM2_INTERNAL_STATE_DO_NOT_USE_OR_PROGRAM_WILL_FAIL variable, which exposes internal security functions (handleException, wrapWith, import). This vulnerability is fixed in 3.11.0.",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-44003**\n| Severity | Package | Fixed Version | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n|MEDIUM|vm2|3.11.0|[CVE-2026-44003](https://avd.aquasec.com/nvd/cve-2026-44003)|\n\nvm2 is an open source vm/sandbox for Node.js. Prior to 3.11.0, vm2's code transformer has a performance optimization that skips AST analysis when the code does not contain catch, import, or async keywords. This fast-path bypass allows sandboxed code to directly access the internal VM2_INTERNAL_STATE_DO_NOT_USE_OR_PROGRAM_WILL_FAIL variable, which exposes internal security functions (handleException, wrapWith, import). This vulnerability is fixed in 3.11.0."
              },
